text: Harry Keller Hoch (January 9, 1887 – October 26, 1981) was an American professional baseball player and lawyer. He played as a pitcher. He played in Major League Baseball (MLB) for the Philadelphia Phillies (1908) and St. Louis Browns (1914–1915). Hoch was born in Woodside, Delaware. He died on October 26, 1981 in Lewes, Delaware, at the age of 94. ==References== ==Other websites== Category:1887 births Category:1981 deaths Category:American baseball players Category:Lawyers from Delaware Category:Philadelphia Phillies players Category:Sportspeople from Delaware Category:St. Louis Browns
